From 1b8c67469d3ac55915c50bcf4a53bb870a5b2a98 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sebastian Bresin <sebastian.bresin@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 17 Feb 2026 11:53:26 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] feat: add 'leadingspacewidth' buffer option (lsw)

Add a new buffer-local option that controls the visual width of leading
space characters without modifying buffer content. When set to N > 0,
each leading space renders as N screen columns wide. Default is 0
(disabled). Abbreviation: lsw.

This is useful when working with codebases that use narrow space
indentation (e.g. 2-space) but you prefer a wider visual indent.
With 2-space indentation and lsw=2, each indent level displays as
4 columns wide.

Implementation:
- Option definition in options.lua with buffer-local scope
- Global var p_lsw, buffer field b_p_lsw, get_varp_from/buf_copy/validate
- CharsizeArg extended with leading_space_end/leading_space_width
- init_charsize_arg scans leading spaces, forces kCharsizeRegular
- charsize_regular returns lsw width for leading space characters
- drawline.c: leadcol computation + n_extra expansion after listchars
- Listchars composition: checks original buffer byte not substituted mb_c
- indent_size_ts extended with lsw param for breakindent integration
- All callers of indent_size_ts updated (indent.c, change.c)
- Breakindent cache invalidation for prev_lsw
- 17 functional UI tests covering rendering, listchars, cursor, options

Ref: neovim#15353
